      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        14221,
        14282
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"access-headers\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>How to: Access custom parameters"
    },
    {
      "content": "When you send a request to your mobile service, you can include custom parameters in the URI of the request to instruct your table operation scripts how to process a given request.",
      "pos": [
        14284,
        14464
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You then modify your script to inspect the parameter to determine the processing path.",
      "pos": [
        14465,
        14551
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        14553,
        14698
      ],
      "content": "For example, the following URI for a POST request tells the service to not permit the insertion of a new <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>TodoItem<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept> that has the same text value:"
    },
    {
      "content": "These custom query parameters are accessed as JSON values from the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>parameters<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> property of the <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p2\">request object]</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        14779,
        14894
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>request<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> object is supplied by Mobile Services to any function registered to a table operation.",
      "pos": [
        14895,
        14997
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following server script for the insert operation checks the value of the <ph id=\"ph1\">`duplicateText`</ph> parameter before the insert operation is run:",
      "pos": [
        14998,
        15136
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        16234,
        16471
      ],
      "content": "Note that in <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>insertItemIfNotComplete<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> the <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>execute<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept> function of the <bpt id=\"p3\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p3\">request object]</ept> is invoked to insert the item when there is no duplicate text; otherwise the <bpt id=\"p4\">**</bpt>respond<ept id=\"p4\">**</ept> function is invoked to notify the client of the duplicate."
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        16474,
        16548
      ],
      "content": "Note the syntax of the call to the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>success<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> function in the above code:"
    },
    {
      "content": "In JavaScript it is a compact version of the lengthier equivalent:",
      "pos": [
        16650,
        16716
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        16828,
        16881
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"work-with-users\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>How to: Work with users"
    },
    {
      "content": "In Azure Mobile Services, you can use an identity provider to authenticate users.",
      "pos": [
        16883,
        16964
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">Get started with authentication]</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        16965,
        17025
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When an authenticated user invokes a table operation, Mobile Services uses the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">user object]</ept> to supply information about the user to the registered script function.",
      "pos": [
        17026,
        17190
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>userId<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> property can be used to store and retrieve user-specific information.",
      "pos": [
        17191,
        17275
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following example sets the owner property of an item based on the userId of an authenticated user:",
      "pos": [
        17276,
        17378
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The next example adds an additional filter to the query based on the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>userId<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> of an authenticated user.",
      "pos": [
        17491,
        17596
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This filter restricts the result to only items that belong to the current user:",
