    },
    {
      "pos": [
        18249,
        18306
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"custom-api-overview\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Overview of custom APIs"
    },
    {
      "content": "A custom API is an endpoint in your mobile service that is accessed by one or more of the standard HTTP methods: GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE.",
      "pos": [
        18308,
        18451
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A separate function export can be defined for each HTTP method supported by the custom API, all in a single script file.",
      "pos": [
        18452,
        18572
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The registered script is invoked when a request to the custom API using the given method is received.",
      "pos": [
        18573,
        18674
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">Custom API]</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        18675,
        18714
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When custom API functions are called by the Mobile Services runtime, both a <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>request<ept id=\"p1\">][request object]</ept> and <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt>response<ept id=\"p2\">][response object]</ept> object are supplied.",
      "pos": [
        18716,
        18870
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "These objects expose the functionality of the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">express.js library]</ept>, which can be leveraged by your scripts.",
      "pos": [
        18871,
        18978
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following custom API named <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>hello<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> is a very simple example that returns <bpt id=\"p2\">_</bpt>Hello, world!<ept id=\"p2\">_</ept> in response to a POST request:",
      "pos": [
        18979,
        19104
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>send<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> function on the <bpt id=\"p2\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p2\">response object]</ept> returns your desired response to the client.",
      "pos": [
        19235,
        19326
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This code is invoked by sending a POST request to the following URL:",
      "pos": [
        19327,
        19395
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The global state is maintained between executions.",
      "pos": [
        19452,
        19502
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        19508,
        19567
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"define-custom-api\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>How to: Define a custom API"
    },
    {
      "content": "You can define server scripts that are registered to HTTP methods in a custom API endpoint in one of the following ways:",
      "pos": [
        19569,
        19689
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure Management Portal<ept id=\"p1\">][Management Portal]</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        19693,
        19745
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Custom API scripts are created and modified in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>API<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab.",
      "pos": [
        19746,
        19809
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The server script code is in the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Scripts<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> tab of a given custom API.",
      "pos": [
        19810,
        19881
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The following shows the script that is invoked by a POST request to the <ph id=\"ph1\">`CompleteAll`</ph> custom API endpoint.",
      "pos": [
        19882,
        19988
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "![2][2]",
      "pos": [
        19995,
        20002
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Access permissions to custom API methods are assigned in the Permissions tab.",
      "pos": [
        20012,
        20089
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To see how this custom API was created, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">Call a custom API from the client]</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        20090,
        20170
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "By using source control.",
      "pos": [
        20176,
        20200
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you have source control enabled, simply create a file named <ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;em&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">`&lt;custom_api&gt;`</ph><ph id=\"ph3\">&lt;/em&gt;</ph>.js in the .\\service\\api subfolder in your git repository, where <ph id=\"ph4\">&lt;em&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph5\">`&lt;custom_api&gt;`</ph><ph id=\"ph6\">&lt;/em&gt;</ph> is the name of the custom API being registered.",
      "pos": [
        20201,
        20425
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This script file contains an <bpt id=\"p1\">_</bpt>exported<ept id=\"p1\">_</ept> function for each HTTP method exposed by the custom API.",
      "pos": [
        20426,
        20522
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Permissions are defined in a companion .json file.",
      "pos": [
        20523,
        20573
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information, see [Source control and shared code][Source control, shared code, and helper functions].",
      "pos": [
        20574,
        20684
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "From the command prompt by using the Azure command line tool.",
      "pos": [
        20688,
        20749
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For more information, see [Using the command line tool].",
      "pos": [
        20750,
