      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a name=\"TSQL\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Using Transact-SQL to access tables"
    },
    {
      "content": "The easiest way to work table data from server scripts is by using a <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">table object]</ept> proxy.",
      "pos": [
        47421,
        47511
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, there are more advanced scenarios that are not supported by the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">table object]</ept>, such as as join queries and other complex queries and invoking stored procedures.",
      "pos": [
        47512,
        47682
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In these cases, you must execute Transact-SQL statements directly against the relational table by using the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt><ept id=\"p1\">mssql object]</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        47683,
